race.comment: THORAX (3) caught the eye with a strong debut win as a short-priced favourite over 1200m here on his home track four weeks ago. Has plenty of promise, and from a good draw, he can take the next step immediately. LUCULLAN (6) has yet to reproduce his good trial form on race day this season, finishing out of the placings as the favourite over 1000m at Trentham nearly 4 weeks ago. There will be no excuses third up from a spell, and with the aid of a 2kg claim, he is worth another chance. FANCYPANTS (10) has not had much luck recently and has the blinkers off here. If he can settle closer with some cover this time, then a form reversal would be no surprise. FIRST GEAR (8) has needed both of his runs back from a spell, and he has been close up in a trial since his most recent outing at Hawera 7 weeks ago. Stick with him. KASUKEDO (1) was less than a length from the winner when finishing fourth here 17 days ago over 1400m. He slides back in class and can figure in the top 3 this time.
